    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presented is an exceptional 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a purist\u2019s configuration featuring the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant. This engine utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, providing a seamless power band. The drivetrain is anchored by a G96/01 six-speed manual transaxle, exhibiting crisp gate engagement and zero bearing noise. Critical preventative measures have been addressed, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The chassis dynamics remain sharp, with the factory-spec multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts maintaining original geometry and damping rates. Braking performance is superlative, utilizing four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled, ventilated rotors with no evidence of thermal glazing. This is a mechanically flawless example with pristine underbody components and factory-spec tolerances throughout.",
      "price": 48500.0,
